    {
      "name": "Keycloak (auth)",
      "description": "Inspect the Keycloak realm provisioned by the project. Run 'Get admin token' first — it stores the bearer token into the `keycloakAdminToken` collection variable used by the other requests.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "(dev) How to grab wtn_session",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "http://localhost:3000/api/auth/me",
              "host": [
                "http://localhost:3000"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "auth",
                "me"
              ]
            },
            "description": "**Not a real request.** Documents how to populate `wtnSession`:\n\n1. In a browser, navigate to `http://localhost:3000/api/auth/login` and complete the Keycloak login.\n2. Open DevTools → Application → Cookies → http://localhost:3000.\n3. Find the `wtn_session` cookie and copy its value (an opaque 32-byte base64url string).\n4. Paste it into this collection's `wtnSession` variable.\n5. Authenticated requests now resolve through the Next BFF proxy on http://localhost:3000/api/proxy/*.\n\nThe cookie is what links you to the session record in `auth-redis`; the access token never leaves the server. If your session expires, repeat from step 1."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "OIDC discovery",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{keycloakBaseUrl}}/realms/{{keycloakRealm}}/.well-known/openid-configuration",
              "host": [
                "{{keycloakBaseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "realms",
                "{{keycloakRealm}}",
                ".well-known",
                "openid-configuration"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Public OIDC discovery — proves the realm is up and reachable."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get admin token",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (json.access_token) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('keycloakAdminToken', json.access_token);",
                  "    console.log('keycloakAdminToken stored (' + json.access_token.length + ' chars).');",
                  "}",
                  "pm.test('200 OK', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
                  "pm.test('access_token present', function () { pm.expect(json.access_token).to.be.a('string').and.not.be.empty; });"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "urlencoded",
              "urlencoded": [
                {
                  "key": "client_id",
                  "value": "admin-cli",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "key": "username",
                  "value": "{{keycloakAdminUser}}",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "key": "password",
                  "value": "{{keycloakAdminPassword}}",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "key": "grant_type",
                  "value": "password",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{keycloakBaseUrl}}/realms/master/protocol/openid-connect/token",
              "host": [
                "{{keycloakBaseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "realms",
                "master",
                "protocol",
                "openid-connect",
                "token"
              ]
            },
            "description": "ROPC against the *master* realm using the built-in `admin-cli` client. Stores `access_token` into the `keycloakAdminToken` collection variable."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "List users (realm)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{keycloakAdminToken}}"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{keycloakBaseUrl}}/admin/realms/{{keycloakRealm}}/users",
